1) Interaction Overview
This is a single-page “GenAI Chatbot” simulation that shows one preset task. When a user clicks the preset task button, the prompt auto-fills into the message input, then auto-sends, shows a typing indicator, and finally shows a fixed bot response.
In the bot response, specific phrases become highlighted and clickable in staged phases. Clicking a highlight opens a “Spotting hidden risks” pop-up that explains the risk, and locks scrolling until dismissed.
2) Screen Map and Layout
•	Regions and scroll areas
o	Full-height layout: at least the viewport height, and must be able to extend vertically beyond the viewport when content requires (e.g., at 320px width / 400% zoom) without clipping or trapping content.Main content padding: 1.5rem 1rem.
o	A main chat “window” fills available space.
o	The message area scrolls vertically (overflow-y: auto).
o	The chat footer stays below the message area (not inside the scroll area).
•	Major components and where they appear
o	Title bar at the top of the chat window, showing:
	Header text: “GenAI Chatbot”
	Helper text: “See the risks when GenAI helps with these tasks”
o	Scrollable messages area below the title bar.
o	Footer area below the message area containing:
	A preset prompt button (when visible).
	The message input and “send” control
•	Key size/constraint rules
o	Messages column max width: 48rem (centered with margin: 0 auto).
o	Chat bubble max width: 32rem.
o	Input min-height: 56px.
o	Input max-height: 200px.
o	Risk pop-up width: min(22rem, 90vw).
o	Avatar size: 2.25rem × 2.25rem.
o	“Send” control size: 2.5rem × 2.5rem.
o	Risk pop-up minimize control size: 2rem × 2rem.
o	Typing dot size: 0.5rem × 0.5rem.
o	Attachment icon size: 1rem × 1rem.
o	Bot/user icon inside avatar: 1.25rem × 1.25rem.
•	Typography and colour defaults:
